TaskFlow is a project management tool I built to explore real-time collaboration patterns and AI integration in modern web applications.

## The Problem

Existing project management tools felt either too complex (Jira) or too simple (Trello). I wanted something in between—powerful enough for engineering teams but intuitive enough that you don't need documentation to use it.

## Key Features

### Real-time Kanban Boards
Multiple team members can collaborate on the same board simultaneously. Changes appear instantly across all connected clients using WebSocket subscriptions.

### AI Task Prioritization
An AI assistant analyzes your task descriptions and suggests priority levels based on urgency keywords, dependencies, and historical patterns.

### Smart Notifications
Instead of notification spam, TaskFlow batches updates intelligently and only alerts you about things that actually need your attention.

### Time Tracking
Built-in time tracking with automatic reminders. Integrates with calendar apps to provide accurate estimates for future planning.

## Technical Architecture

```
┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
│           Next.js Frontend              │
│         (React Server Components)       │
└─────────────────┬───────────────────────┘
                  │
┌─────────────────▼───────────────────────┐
│            API Routes                    │
│         (tRPC + WebSockets)             │
└─────────────────┬───────────────────────┘
                  │
┌─────────────────▼───────────────────────┐
│            PostgreSQL                    │
│         (Drizzle ORM)                   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

## Lessons Learned

- **Optimistic UI updates** dramatically improve perceived performance for collaborative features
- **WebSocket connection management** is tricky—you need robust reconnection logic
- **AI features work best** when they augment, not replace, user decisions

## What's Next

